    "description_long": "This is a rectangular caution sign mounted on a vertical, ribbed black pole. The sign face is white with a bold red circle and diagonal slash, indicating prohibition, over a black icon of a person discarding trash. Below the symbol, the words 'NO LITTERING' are printed in uppercase black letters. The sign is bordered with a thin black outline, enhancing its visibility. The pole appears to be made of metal, providing stability and durability for outdoor urban environments. The back of the sign is plain and unmarked, with the mounting hardware not visible from the front.",
